# 4. Variance partitioning (Figure 5)

Distance-based RDA on the microbiome distance matrix, partitioned between
Season and the leading diet PCoA axes.

```{r dbrda-varpart}
diet_pcoa <- cmdscale(diet_asv_dist_common, k = 5, eig = TRUE)
diet_axes <- as.data.frame(diet_pcoa$points)

# dbRDA: diet axes constrained, Season as conditioning factor
dbrda_res <- vegan::dbrda(
  microbiome_asv_dist_common ~ . + Condition(meta_common$Season),
  data = diet_axes
)

anova(dbrda_res, permutations = 999)
anova(dbrda_res, by = "axis", permutations = 999)
RsquareAdj(dbrda_res)

# Variance partitioning: Season vs diet axes
varp <- varpart(
  microbiome_asv_dist_common,
  ~ Season,
  diet_axes,
  data = data.frame(Season = meta_common$Season, diet_axes)
)
varp
plot(varp)
```

